  "description": "<i>In Nihilum Reverteris</i> is a text based adventure game. The game form is similar to a Gamebook - a long paragraphs of text, supplemented with graphic pictures and a choice to make every once in a while. The protagonist of the story is Karl, a science fiction writer. The main axis of the story is his efforts to explain the essence and the causes of the series of unusual events that he is witnessing.<br><br>The game has been designed for TV-sets and RGB monitors.  \nAtari version has one more picture implemented and 11 sound tracks all together (ZX Spectrum just 1).<br><br>",
